text.__SUMMARY__: Conus alexandrei is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Conidae, the cone snails, cone shells or cones.
text.Description: The size of the shell varies between 30 mm and 46 mm.
text.Distribution: This marine species occurs off the Philippines, Fiji and Vanuatu
text.References:
Limpalaër L. & Monnier E. (2012) Phasmoconus alexandrei (Gastropoda: Conidae), a new species from the western Pacific. Visaya 3(5): 21-27.
